cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.CC, cs.CR 

This paper investigates the perception of workers in an online labor market, specifically Amazon Mechanical Turk, towards online employers and employers in their host country in terms of honesty and fairness. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the social and ethical aspects of computing. The paper also touches upon human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it studies the interaction between workers and online employers. The use of surveys and statistical analysis suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the potential abuses and exploitation in online labor markets, which may fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
